# UI and product identity

TYPELY = pastel, playful, robot, educational, glassmorphism. BauHub =
dark, futuristic, ecosystem. Do not collapse the two into a generic
corporate dashboard. Match the existing visual system in
`src/styles/global.css` (Fredoka + Nunito, the color tokens, radius,
shadow, and gradient rules) and never draw islands or mascots with CSS.

Popups and modals must scroll when their content exceeds the viewport
height (use `max-height: 88vh; overflow-y: auto` style caps, the same as
the existing admin modals). Buttons must remain reachable — never let
fixed UI cover important interactive elements.

Animations: use `animejs` / `framer-motion` only where they add value.
Avoid janky scroll, teleporting elements, infinite distracting loops, and
heavy animations that hurt performance. Honour
`prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` for entrance animations.

Avoid UI accumulation: cap visible toasts (the existing `Toast`
component already does this), and make sure intervals, animation loops,
and event listeners clean up on unmount.
